10.18.16  9:10 pm   this morning I was feeling pretty shitty about everything, but then I got a good grade on a test and felt better. but THEN, after another hour, I started to feel shitty again because the only thing that had cheered me up was a number that somebody stamped on my level of understanding of a concept. (does that make sense?) I feel that way a lot when I'm making music - like I shouldn't care what people think and that I should just do what I know feels right, but then crippled when the things I make aren't liked OR affirmed when they are. you're in an interesting position because you claim not to give a shit (which I honestly believe is true) but people still love your work and tell you that all the time. you make whatever you want, but "whatever you want" wins awards. what should I do? how do I ignore them? or how do I balance these two contradictory parts of my brain? OR how do I succeed at making things and feeling like they matter even if they aren't accessible or liked?
